  "why": "The paper demonstrates cross-model transferability by reusing fault-inducing inputs discovered on the 32-bit model to trigger failures (prediction disagreements) in the 16-bit quantized version. However, the fuzzing design does not include explicit mechanisms (e.g., surrogate-model-guided mutation) to promote transferable attack discovery; it uses the activations of the single model under test as its coverage signal. Thus it empirically shows transferability without explicitly designing for it.",
